<item>
            <title>[HBASE-3246] Add API to Increment client class that increments rather than replaces the amount for a column when done multiple times</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3246</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the new Increment class, the API to add columns is &lt;tt&gt;addColumn()&lt;/tt&gt;.  If you do this multiple times for an individual column, the amount to increment by is replaced.  I think this is the right way for this method to work and it is javadoc&apos;d with the behavior.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should add a new method, &lt;tt&gt;incrementColumn()&lt;/tt&gt; which will increment any existing amount for the specified column rather than replacing it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12480367">HBASE-3246</key>
