                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12933546" author="streamy" created="Thu, 18 Nov 2010 19:52:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Writing the javadoc for these methods, it seems like people could get easily confused.  Probably should have called the original method &lt;tt&gt;incrementColumn()&lt;/tt&gt; and then just add a second method w/ a boolean about whether you want to sum with existing or replace existing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Will put up a patch with what I came up based on my original description with but could use some input from others.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12933549" author="streamy" created="Thu, 18 Nov 2010 19:58:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached patch does what is described in the description.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I tried to be super explicit in the javadoc about exactly what is happening, including adding more info to the existing method.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also one minor change to existing method.  Only do the put into the Map if it didn&apos;t already exist.  Doesn&apos;t change behavior but is more &quot;optimal&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12933618" author="stack" created="Fri, 19 Nov 2010 00:07:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;There&apos;ll only be one thread in here at a time?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12933645" author="khemani" created="Fri, 19 Nov 2010 01:15:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;is there any need for addColumn()? it might be cleaner to just have incrementColumn() in this API&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12935136" author="streamy" created="Tue, 23 Nov 2010 23:52:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I would be okay with just removing addColumn and having a single call, incrementColumn().  That method would be additive w/ existing calls for a given column.  If you wanted to somehow undo existing increments of columns, you would have to start over with a new Increment.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I could also add a separate call, resetColumn() but then we start to get more confusing again.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Everyone okay with removing addColumn() and just leaving incrementColumn()?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12935137" author="streamy" created="Tue, 23 Nov 2010 23:54:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Stack, and yeah, all of our client classes are not thread-safe.  If you wanted to use an Increment across threads you&apos;d have to do your own synchronization, but I think that would be kind of odd.  Can add a note that class is not thread-safe in the javadoc.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12935182" author="stack" created="Wed, 24 Nov 2010 03:33:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m fine w/ removing addColumn.  Lets get the change in before we cut new RC.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14067278" author="apurtell" created="Sat, 19 Jul 2014 00:27:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Didn&apos;t happen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
